<L>__{exterior rosemond estate aerial shot day}
<A>__{we move across the sky looking down at lush greens and stately mansions till we pass over the rosemond estate. enormous in size. we see two riders on horseback.}
<L>__{exterior estate meadow day}
<A>__{angle on: the two horseback riders. one, a woman of seventy. this is helen rosemond, sebastian's aunt. the other rider is a beautiful seventeen year old girl. the one and only annette harrison.}
<C>__{annette}
<D>__{it's a beautiful home you have here mrs. rosemond.}
<C>__{aunt helen}
<D>__{thank you, annette. chance hill has been with my family for over sixty years. does your family do much riding?}
<C>__{annette}
<D>__{my mother and i used to ride a lot, before she got sick.}
<C>__{aunt helen}
<D>__{i'm sorry about that.}
<C>__{annette}
<D>__{my grandpa, used to breed horses on his farm so i would come over and ride all the time.}
<C>__{aunt helen}
<D>__{i'm familiar with a lot of breeders in the mid west. what's his name?}
<C>__{annette}
<D>__{ben schwarz.}
<C>__{aunt helen}
<D>__{schwarz. jewish?}
<C>__{annette}
<D>__{german.}
<C>__{aunt helen}
<D>__{doesn't ring a bell.}
<A>__{annette throws her a concerned look.}
<C>__{aunt helen }
<D>__{in any event, i want you to consider this your home for the time being.}
<C>__{annette}
<D>__{thank you. it's so peaceful and quiet around here.}
<A>__{bang! a shotgun sounds in the distance.}
<C>__{annette }
<D>__{what was that?}
<C>__{aunt helen}
<D>__{sebastian must be here.}
<A>__{aunt helen gallops down the ridge followed by annette.}
